  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.__dict__ membership for result/exception methods in cfrepr207 namespace — Future.__dict__.__contains__('set_result')==True (Future.set_result() sets the return value of the work and notifies done callbacks; defined directly in _base.py); Future.__dict__.__contains__('set_exception')==True (Future.set_exception() sets an exception result and notifies callbacks); Future.__dict__.__contains__('result')==True (Future.result() returns the value set by set_result()); Future.__dict__.__contains__('exception')==True (Future.exception() returns the exception raised or None); all four are in Future.__dict__; verified with Python 3.14.3"
